  ('mark-twain-house', 'Mark Twain House', 'Hartford', '351 Farmington Avenue', 'CT', 41.7672, -72.7014, 'museum', 'The Victorian Gothic home where Samuel Clemens (Mark Twain) lived from 1874 to 1891, writing many of his greatest works including "Adventures of Huckleberry Finn." The 25-room mansion features elaborate interior design by Louis Comfort Tiffany.', 'The smell of cigar smoke permeates several parts of the house despite smoking being banned - Twain reportedly smoked up to 40 cigars a day. A Lady in White in period dress has been seen walking through rooms before vanishing. Visitors and staff report seeing Twain''s ghost and that of his daughter Susy, who died in the house at age 24. The butler George Griffin is blamed for phantom knocks and loud banging sounds. Featured on Ghost Hunters and Ghost Hunters Academy.', 1874, 'https://marktwainhouse.org/'),

  ('old-state-house-hartford', 'Old State House', 'Hartford', '800 Main Street', 'CT', 41.7658, -72.6734, 'historic_site', 'Completed in 1796, Connecticut''s Old State House is one of the oldest state houses in the nation. Designed by Charles Bulfinch, the building served as Connecticut''s capitol until 1878 and now operates as a museum complex.', 'Ghost Hunters visited the Old State House based on reports from former staff members. During their investigation, the team heard sounds of door knobs opening and saw a woman in the building when it should have been empty. Visitors have reported strange footsteps and sounds of ghostly assembly meetings occurring in empty halls. The building''s long history of political gatherings seems to echo through time.', 1796, 'https://www.ctinsider.com/living/article/haunted-hartford-ct-state-house-mark-twain-18414902.php'),

  ('hartford-elks-lodge', 'Hartford Elks Lodge', 'Hartford', '148 Prospect Street', 'CT', 41.7700, -72.6891, 'other', 'A historic fraternal organization building on Prospect Street that has served the Hartford community for over a century. The lodge maintains traditions dating back to the late 1800s while also maintaining some supernatural residents.', 'Another Hartford location investigated by the Ghost Hunters TV show, the Hartford Elks Lodge is said to be haunted by a former member of the lodge who refuses to leave. Staff and members have reported unexplained phenomena including doors opening and closing, footsteps in empty hallways, and the feeling of being watched during late-night events.', 1890, 'https://www.ctinsider.com/living/article/haunted-hartford-ct-state-house-mark-twain-18414902.php');

