  ('union-cemetery-easton', 'Union Cemetery', 'Easton', '1 Stepney Road', 'CT', 41.2589, -73.2975, 'cemetery', 'Dating back to the 1760s, Union Cemetery in Easton is considered one of the most haunted cemeteries in the United States. Famed paranormal investigators Ed and Lorraine Warren called it one of the most haunted places around.', 'The infamous "White Lady" haunts both the cemetery and nearby Route 59, wearing a white nightgown with long dark hair. In 1993, an off-duty fireman''s vehicle made impact with her apparition, leaving a dent in his car. Ed Warren captured her on film in 1990. A second entity called "Red Eyes" peers from nearby underbrush with glowing crimson eyes. Soldiers on horseback and giggling children have also been reported.', 1760, 'https://www.ctinsider.com/living/article/ct-white-lady-union-cemetery-urban-legend-17533746.php'),

  ('sheffield-island-lighthouse', 'Sheffield Island Lighthouse', 'Norwalk', 'Sheffield Island', 'CT', 41.0486, -73.4172, 'lighthouse', 'Activated in 1868, the Sheffield Island Lighthouse served for 34 years before retirement in 1902. Named to the National Register of Historic Places, the lighthouse is maintained by the Norwalk Seaport Association and named one of the most haunted places in America by Conde Nast Traveler.', 'In 1991, an archaeologist heard mysterious music, a nonexistent foghorn, and distant cries for help with no one in sight. Captain Robert Sheffield, who purchased the island in the early 1800s and was known for his eccentric love of unusual musical instruments, is believed responsible. A 2006 paranormal investigation found three friendly spirits including a young girl named Abby who is trapped on the island for unknown reasons.', 1868, 'https://patch.com/connecticut/norwalk/sheffield-lighthouse-haunted'),

  ('boothe-memorial-park', 'Boothe Memorial Park', 'Stratford', '5800 Main Street', 'CT', 41.2083, -73.1308, 'park', 'Labeled "the oldest homestead in America," Boothe Memorial Park sits on a foundation dating to 1663 and features unusual architecture including a mini windmill, clock tower, lighthouse, and a building with no windows or doors. The Boothe brothers were heavily interested in spiritualism.', 'The Boothe brothers built shrines throughout the property, which is said to have caused the area''s haunted nature. Visitors report unexplained knocking and disembodied voices. Paranormal investigators have captured Class A EVPs and witnessed orbs. One investigator reported a ball of light passing through him. A creepy old organ in one cottage adds to the unnerving atmosphere.', 1663, 'https://www.damnedct.com/boothe-memorial-park-stratford/'),

  ('remington-arms-factory', 'Remington Arms Factory', 'Bridgeport', '939 Barnum Avenue', 'CT', 41.1867, -73.1747, 'other', 'This former weapons factory was closed in the 1980s following numerous fatal accidents, including workers falling into kettles of molten metal and a 1942 explosion that killed seven workers. The abandoned building was featured on Ghost Adventures.', 'Shadowy figures are frequently seen in the abandoned buildings. The sounds of weapon-factory work continue despite the factory being silent for decades - machinery running, talking voices, and yelling. A cemetery across the street contains the grave of a woman allegedly buried alive. Ghost Adventures documented extensive paranormal activity throughout the complex.', 1867, 'https://www.damnedct.com/remington-arms-bridgeport/'),

  ('sterling-opera-house', 'Sterling Opera House', 'Derby', '77 Elizabeth Street', 'CT', 41.3264, -73.0878, 'theater', 'Built in 1889, the Sterling Opera House was the first building added to the National Register of Historic Places in November 1968. In its heyday, it welcomed Harry Houdini and Red Skelton until closing in 1945. The building has sat empty and decaying since.', 'Those who have visited the defunct theater report seeing orbs of light and apparitions, and hearing the voices of children. The empty stage seems to still echo with performances from over a century ago. Shadow figures move through the deteriorating auditorium. The tragedy of the theater''s abandonment seems to have trapped its former glory within its walls.', 1889, 'https://www.ctinsider.com/entertainment/article/Connecticut-s-haunted-nature-lies-in-its-history-16559062.php');

