  ('lighthouse-inn-new-london', 'The Lighthouse Inn', 'New London', '6 Guthrie Place', 'CT', 41.3192, -72.0867, 'hotel', 'Originally built in 1902 as a summer estate called Meadow Court by Charles Guthrie, the property attracted celebrities like Bette Davis and Joan Crawford. In 1927, it transformed into a hotel and gained a ghostly reputation.', 'A bride who fell to her death on the inn''s staircase in the early 1900s still haunts the property. Guests and staff report sightings of her ghost in a white gown wandering the halls. She has been featured on Ghost Hunters. The romantic tragedy of her wedding day death seems to keep her spirit bound to the elegant inn.', 1902, 'https://www.hauntedrooms.com/connecticut/haunted-places/haunted-hotels/'),

  ('griswold-inn', 'The Griswold Inn', 'Essex', '36 Main Street', 'CT', 41.3514, -72.3908, 'hotel', 'One of the oldest continuously operated inns in the United States, the Griswold Inn has hosted sailors, soldiers, and travelers since 1776. The historic tavern retains its colonial charm while harboring spirits from centuries past.', 'Guests have reported seeing ghostly figures in colonial attire, hearing footsteps in empty hallways, and experiencing sudden drops in temperature. The most famous tale involves a spectral sea captain who appears near the inn''s fireplace, looking out longingly as if waiting for a ship that will never return. The inn''s centuries of hosting travelers has left many spirits behind.', 1776, 'https://www.hauntedrooms.com/connecticut/haunted-places/haunted-hotels/'),

